message.body: And that seemed to have done it.
Are you getting these as well?
How's it going?
Hello?
How was your fri night?
It was okay. I actually went on a blind date for the first time in my life, which went pretty well.
How about you?
I was hanging out with Nina, it was fun.
Blind date sounds scary!
Nice, I just got to see her at our show a couple weeks ago, which was really nice.
Yeah, in general blind dates have never been something I'd be interested in, but a friend of mine set us up and so I agreed.
Yeah she mentioned that, sorry i missed yr show btw!
But it definitely wasn't a horror story. It was just kind of pleasant.
You think you'll go out again?
Yeah, I think possibly in a couple of weeks. I don't think either of us are completely sold on the situation yet, but willing to see type of thing.
Regarding the show, it's all good that you missed. I was extremely scattered and late for the show, but it ended up going ok in the end.
It felt good to actually get all the way through the set, but leading up I was kind of disastrous. I actually have another show tonight.
My phone is being kinda weird, i havta get a new one asap
I dunno if it's my phone, but I don't think you got my last txts
Hm, there was a delay (and I moved to a different area of the library). The last ones I got were "think you'll go out again" and "phone is being weird.
Are there ones I missed?
Yeah, I asked where your show is tonight
Ah, in Ardmore at a place called the Rusty Nail. It's a friend's birthday and his band played at the house with us.
It's going to be a bit weird, I think. There are four acts playing who are friends, and then there's a typical dive bar band playing after us.
But it should be fun.
Is ardmore on the main line?
To be honest, I'm not sure.
I always confuse all these pa suburbs
Google shows it in the Northwest of Philly. West of Bala Cynwyd and North of Drexel Hill/Havertown.
Do you have any plans for the rest of the weekend?
Ah makes sense think i know someone who lives out there, now that i think aboyut it
going to try to get a new phone tomorrow
And spend some time outside, it's sooo nice out. Just got in from the park with the dog
what about you?
It is ridiculously nice. I'm just trying to finish up the video part of my set tonight, play the show and rest up tomorrow.
Probably clean my room tomorrow since I've been hecticly throwing stuff all over the place the past couple days. Return some order to my life.
sounds good. I gotta go!
ttyl
